BEGIN_PGML Simplify [`\definecolor{sapphire}{RGB}{59,90,125}\newcommand{\abs}[1]{\left\lvert#1\right\rvert}\dfrac{2\abs{9-15}+1}{\sqrt{(-5)^2+12^2}}\text{.}`]
[_]{1}{10}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION To simplify this expression, the first thing we want to recognize is the role of the main fraction bar, which groups the numerator and denominator. This implies we'll simplify the numerator and denominator separately according to the order of operations, and then reduce the fraction that results:
[```\definecolor{sapphire}{RGB}{59,90,125}\newcommand{\abs}[1]{\left\lvert#1\right\rvert}\newcommand{\highlight}[1]{\mathchoice{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\displaystyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\textstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptscriptstyle #1$}}}\newcommand{\nextoperation}[1]{\mathord{\boxed{#1}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&} \begin{aligned} \frac{2\abs{9-15}+1}{\sqrt{(-5)^2+12^2}}\amp=\frac{2\abs{\nextoperation{9-15}}+1}{\sqrt{\nextoperation{(-5)^2}+12^2}}\\ \amp=\frac{2\nextoperation{\abs{\highlight{-6}}}+1}{\sqrt{\highlight{25}+\nextoperation{12^2}}}\\ \amp=\frac{\nextoperation{2(\highlight{6})}+1}{\sqrt{\nextoperation{25+\highlight{144}}}}\\ \amp=\frac{\nextoperation{\highlight{12}+1}}{\nextoperation{\sqrt{\highlight{169}}}}\\ \amp=\frac{\highlight{13}}{\highlight{13}}\\ \amp=\highlight{1} \end{aligned} ```]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
